'''亨利·古斯塔夫·莫萊森'''（{{lang-en|Henry Gustav Molaison}}，{{bd|1926年|2月26日|2008年|12月2日}}），在[[醫學|醫學]]界以 '''H.M.'''知名。他是一位[[美國|美國]]籍的{{link-en|記憶障礙|memory disorder}}患者，原因是因為他曾罹患嚴重的[[癫痫症|癫痫症]]。當時為了治好他的症狀，{{link-en|William Scoville|William Beecher Scoville}}醫生對他施行了雙內側{{link-en|前顳葉切除術|Anterior temporal lobectomy}}，移除了他大腦中三分之二的[[海马体|海马体]] 、[[海马旁回|海马旁回]]、[[內嗅皮層|內嗅皮層]]、{{link-en|梨狀皮質|piriform cortex}}，以及[[杏仁核|杏仁核]]。他自1957年後，開始接受學界對他廣泛的研究，直至於2008年逝世為止。<ref name=carey2>{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/07/science/07memory.html?ref=health | title=No Memory, but He Filled In the Blanks | author=[[Benedict_Carey|Benedict Carey]] | newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] | quote=Henry Gustav Molaison — known through most of his life only as H.M., to protect his privacy — became the most studied patient in the history of brain science after 1953, when an experimental brain operation left him, at age 27, unable to form new declarative memories. ... After repeated trials on the same puzzles, the man who lost his memory learned to fill in the right answers. 'We found that he could learn new semantic, factual information as long as he had something in his memory to anchor it to,' Dr. Skotko said. | date=December 6, 2010 | accessdate=2008-12-05 | archive-date=2018-06-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613210556/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/07/science/07memory.html?ref=health | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=carey>{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/05/us/05hm.html | title=H. M., an Unforgettable Amnesiac, Dies at 82 | author=[[Benedict_Carey|Benedict Carey]] | newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] | quote=In 1953, he underwent an experimental brain operation in Hartford to correct a seizure disorder, only to emerge from it fundamentally and irreparably changed. He developed a syndrome neurologists call profound amnesia. He had lost the ability to form new declarative memories. | date=December 4, 2008 | accessdate=2008-12-05 | archive-date=2018-06-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184944/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/05/us/05hm.html | dead-url=no }}</ref> 他的案例對於大腦在學習[[記憶|記憶]]功能，以及{{link-en|認知神經心理學|cognitive neuropsychology}}（[[心理学|心理学]]的[[分支|分支]]之一，旨在了解大腦的結構和功能，及其與心理學上的關聯）的學術研究方面，佔有非常重要的角色。 他住在{{link-en|溫莎洛克斯 (康乃狄克)|Windsor Locks, Connecticut|溫莎洛克斯}}鎮的一所看護中心，並在那裏作為被研究調查的對象。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.brainconnection.com/topics/?main=fa/hm-memory4 |title=Henry Right Now |accessdate=2008-08-05 |work=The Day His World Stood Still |publisher=BrainConnection.com |first=Joanna |last=Schaffhausen |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080209192921/http://www.brainconnection.com/topics/?main=fa%2Fhm-memory4 |archivedate=2008-02-09 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

2009年12月4日，莫萊森的大腦被保存在[[加利福尼亞大學聖地牙哥分校|加利福尼亞大學聖地牙哥分校]]<ref name="Courant_obit">{{Cite news |url=http://www.courant.com/health/hc-hm-brain-internet-1129.artnov29,0,976422,full.story |title=Researchers To Study Pieces Of Unique Brain |date=November 29, 2009 |author=Arielle Levin Becker |work=The Hartford Courant |access-date=2015-05-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100106080452/http://www.courant.com/health/hc-hm-brain-internet-1129.artnov29,0,976422,full.story |archive-date=2010-01-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，研究者可在該校找到相關的資料<ref>[http://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2014/01/hm-brain-closeup/#x Scientists Digitize Psychology’s Most Famous Brain] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2014/01/hm-brain-closeup/#x |date=20140317024031 }}, Wired.com</ref>，另一個在死後得到同等待遇的人是[[愛因斯坦|愛因斯坦]]<ref>{{cite news|author1=新京報|title=目擊!切開最珍貴大腦 網絡直播40萬人觀看|url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/10569712.html|accessdate=2015-05-18|agency=[[新京報|新京報]]|publisher=[[人民網|人民網]]|date=2009-12-14|archive-date=2018-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930091612/http://scitech.people.com.cn/BIG5/10569712.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 生平 ==
[[File:Hippolobes.gif|right]]的大部分。]]
莫萊森生於1926年2月26日，7歲時因為一次[[自行車|自行車]]事故而得了頑固型[[癲癇|癲癇]]。（對於此事故，早期的報導指是於9歲時發生，後來在患者母親的指正下改為7歲<ref name=corkin>{{Cite journal
  | last = Corkin
  | first = Suzanne
  | title = Lasting consequences of bilateral medial temporal lobectomy: Clinical course and experimental findings in H.M.
  | journal = Seminars in Neurology
  | volume = 4
  | issue = 4
  | pages = 249–259
  | publisher = Thieme-Stratton Inc.
  | location = New York, NY
  | year = 1984
  | doi = 10.1055/s-2008-1041556
}}</ref>）。此後，他就為{{link-en|局部癲癇發作|Partial seizure|局部發作}}癲癇所苦；16歲生日後，又發生了幾次{{link-en|僵直陣攣癲癇發作|Tonic–clonic seizure|僵直性癲癇}}。1953年，他開始接受{{link-en|哈特福醫院|Hartford Hospital}}[[神經外科|神經外科]]一位名叫{{link-en|威廉·畢雪·史可維爾|William Beecher Scoville}}（William Beecher Scoville）醫生的治療。<ref name=carey/>

史可維爾醫生認為，莫萊森的癲癇與左右腦的「內側中央[[顳葉|顳葉]]」（medial temporal lobes，MTLS）有關，故建議切除MTLS。1953年8月25日，27歲的莫萊森接受了雙內側{{link-en|前顳葉切除術|Anterior temporal lobectomy}}，他的{{link-en|海馬構造|Hippocampal formation}}與鄰近組織，大部分的[[杏仁核|杏仁核]]與{{link-en|內鼻皮層|entorhinal cortex}}也被切除。此後，他的海馬體完全無功能，因為剩餘約2[[厘米|厘米]]的海馬組織已萎縮，且負責傳遞感覺給海馬體的內鼻皮層也被損毀，而他的部分[[人体解剖学方位|外側]]顳葉也被破壞。

此次手術，雖然成功的控制了莫萊森的癲癇症狀，但卻帶來了嚴重的痛苦－[[顺行性遗忘症|顺行性遗忘症]]。儘管他的[[工作记忆|工作记忆]]與[[程序記憶|程序記憶]]是完好的，但他無法運用他的[[外顯記憶|外顯記憶]]記住新事物。根據部分科學家的研究，莫萊森學習新[[语义学|語義]]知識的能力受到損害<ref>Schmolck, Kensinger, Corkin, & Squire, 2002</ref> ，但研究人員對損害的程度有爭議。他也有一定程度的[[逆行性失憶症|逆行性失憶症]]障礙，不能記得手術前一至二年前的大部分，與11年前的部分事物，這表示他的[[失憶症|失憶症]]是屬於短期漸進型 （temporally graded）；然而，他的長期[[程序記憶|程序記憶]]能力是完好的，因此他可以學習例如新的[[动作技能|动作技能]]，儘管莫萊森不會記得他曾經學過。

這個案例，是由史可維爾醫生與{{link-en|布倫達·米爾納|Brenda Milner}}（Brenda Milner）在1957年的研究報告中首次提出的<ref name=scoville>{{Cite journal  
 | author = [[William_Beecher_Scoville|William Beecher Scoville]] and [[Brenda_Milner|Brenda Milner]]
 | year = 1957
 | title = Loss of recent memory after bilateral hippocampal lesions
 | journal = [[Journal_of_Neurology,_Neurosurgery_and_Psychiatry|Journal of Neurology, Neurosurgery and Psychiatry]]
 | volume = 20
 | pages = 11–21
 | url = 
 | pmid = 13406589
 | pmc = 497229  
 | doi = 10.1136/jnnp.20.1.11  
 | issue = 1
}}</ref> 。在莫萊森的晚年，他不斷地填寫[[填字遊戲|填字遊戲]]<ref>{{cite news |author= |coauthors= |title=The Man Who Couldn't Remember |url=http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/body/corkin-hm-memory.html |quote=In between it all he did puzzles, books upon books of them, a habit he’d picked up as a teenager. Near the end of his life he kept a crossword book and pen with him always, in a basket attached to his walker. |newspaper=[[NOVA_scienceNOW|NOVA scienceNOW]] |date=June 1, 2009 |accessdate=2010-12-09 |archive-date=2018-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005005347/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/body/corkin-hm-memory.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他能藉由1953年以前學到的知識中得到線索來填寫答案；對於1953年以後的[[資訊|資訊]]，他能修正他的舊記憶與新記憶，例如他曾修正自己對於[[乔纳斯·索尔克|乔纳斯·索尔克]]發明[[小兒麻痺疫苗|小兒麻痺疫苗]]的記憶<ref name=carey2/>。

他於2008年12月2日過世<ref name=carey/>。

